{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775843073841,"sessionID":"ses_28781ead6ffeH8TacWsajPyF7T","part":{"id":"prt_d787edef7001qj8d055HDX9Omx","messageID":"msg_d787ed1310013LUaJVyA7FbnIg","sessionID":"ses_28781ead6ffeH8TacWsajPyF7T","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-cd34a3cacedc447c9631e0d304fd345e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/workloadmanager/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/workloadmanager/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # pkg/workloadmanager — WorkloadManager HTTP Service Framework Design\n2: \n3: ## AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP Service Framework\n4: \n5: **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n6: **Language**: Go  \n7: **Size**: M  \n8: **Purpose**: Provide HTTP API for creating and managing agent runtime sandboxes, implementing session lifecycle management, and integrating with Kubernetes API and Redis storage.\n9: \n10: ## Architecture\n11: \n12: ### Package Structure\n13: \n14: ```\n15: pkg/workloadmanager/\n16: ├── api/\n17: │   ├── agent_runtime.go       # AgentRuntime CRUD handlers\n18: │   ├── code_interpreter.go    # CodeInterpreter CRUD handlers\n19: │   ├── sandbox.go             # Sandbox creation endpoints\n20: │   ├── middleware.go          # Authentication, logging, recovery\n21: │   └── types.go               # API request/response types\n22: ├── controller/\n23: │   ├── agent_runtime.go       # AgentRuntime controller\n24: │   ├── code_interpreter.go    # CodeInterpreter controller\n25: │   ├── sandbox_manager.go     # Sandbox lifecycle management\n26: │   └── session_lifecycle.go   # Session timeout and cleanup\n27: ├── storage/\n28: │   ├── redis.go               # Redis client wrapper\n29: │   ├── session_store.go       # Session storage interface\n30: │   └── metrics.go             # Storage metrics\n31: ├── auth/\n32: │   ├── jwt.go                 # JWT validation and signing\n33: │   ├── k8s_auth.go            # Kubernetes TokenReview integration\n34: │   └── rbac.go                # RBAC enforcement\n35: ├── config/\n36: │   ├── config.go              # Configuration loading\n37: │   └── validation.go          # Config validation\n38: ├── server/\n39: │   ├── server.go              # HTTP server setup\n40: │   ├── router.go              # Route registration\n41: │   └── health.go              # Health check endpoints\n42: └── client/\n43:     ├── k8s_client.go          # Kubernetes client wrapper\n44:     ├── runtime_client.go      # AgentCube runtime client\n45:     └── sandbox_client.go      # Sandbox API client\n46: ```\n47: \n48: ### Component Interactions\n49: \n50: ```\n51: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n52: │                     WorkloadManager HTTP Server                  │\n53: │                                                                  │\n54: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n55: │  │                    Gin HTTP Layer                        │   │\n56: │  │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │   │\n57: │  │  │           Middleware Chain                         │  │   │\n58: │  │  │  Auth → Logging → Recovery → RBAC → Metrics        │  │   │\n59: │  │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │   │\n60: │  │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │   │\n61: │  │  │              API Handlers                          │  │   │\n62: │  │  │  POST /v1/agent-runtime      → CreateSandbox       │  │   │\n63: │  │  │  POST /v1/code-interpreter   → CreateSandbox       │  │   │\n64: │  │  │  GET  /v1/sessions/:id       → GetSession          │  │   │\n65: │  │  │  DELETE /v1/sessions/:id     → DeleteSession       │  │   │\n66: │  │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │   │\n67: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n68: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n69:          │                     │                     │\n70:          │                     │                     │\n71:          ▼                     ▼                     ▼\n72: ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐\n73: │  Kubernetes API  │  │     Redis        │  │   Sandbox API    │\n74: │  (client-go)     │  │   (go-redis)     │  │  (agent-sandbox) │\n75: │  - CRDs          │  │  - Session store │  │  - Pod CRUD      │\n76: │  - Pods          │  │  - Activity TTL  │  │  - Secrets       │\n77: │  - Secrets       │  │  - Metadata      │  │  - TokenReview   │\n78: └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────┘\n79: ```\n80: \n81: ### Request Flow\n82: \n83: ```\n84: Client Request (Router)\n85:     ↓\n86: [Middleware] Auth Validation\n87:     ↓\n88: [Middleware] RBAC Check\n89:     ↓\n90: [Handler] Parse Request\n91:     ↓\n92: [Controller] Validate Spec\n93:     ↓\n94: [Controller] Create Session Record\n95:     ↓\n96: [Controller] Create Sandbox Pod\n97:     ↓\n98: [Controller] Create JWT Token\n99:     ↓\n100: [Controller] Update Session Metadata\n101:     ↓\n102: Response: SandboxInfo + SessionID\n103: ```\n104: \n105: ## Data Structures\n106: \n107: ### API Request/Response Types\n108: \n109: **File**: `pkg/workloadmanager/api/types.go`\n110: \n111: ```go\n112: // CreateSandboxRequest defines the request to create a sandbox\n113: type CreateSandboxRequest struct {\n114:     Kind      string `json:\"kind\" binding:\"required,oneof=AgentRuntime CodeInterpreter\"`\n115:     Name      string `json:\"name\" binding:\"required\"`\n116:     Namespace string `json:\"namespace\" binding:\"required\"`\n117: }\n118: \n119: // CreateSandboxResponse defines the response for sandbox creation\n120: type CreateSandboxResponse struct {\n121:     SessionID  string             `json:\"sessionId\"`\n122:     SandboxID  string             `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n123:     SandboxName string            `json:\"sandboxName\"`\n124:     EntryPoints []types.EntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n125:     CreatedAt  time.Time          `json:\"createdAt\"`\n126:     ExpiresAt  time.Time          `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n127: }\n128: \n129: // GetSessionRequest defines the request to get session info\n130: type GetSessionRequest struct {\n131:     SessionID string `uri:\"sessionId\" binding:\"required\"`\n132: }\n133: \n134: // GetSessionResponse defines the response for session info\n135: type GetSessionResponse struct {\n136:     SessionID    string             `json:\"sessionId\"`\n137:     SandboxID    string             `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n138:     SandboxName  string             `json:\"sandboxName\"`\n139:     Kind         string             `json:\"kind\"`\n140:     Namespace    string             `json:\"namespace\"`\n141:     Name         string             `json:\"name\"`\n142:     EntryPoints  []types.EntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n143:     LastActivity time.Time          `json:\"lastActivity\"`\n144:     CreatedAt    time.Time          `json:\"createdAt\"`\n145:     ExpiresAt    time.Time          `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n146: }\n147: \n148: // DeleteSessionRequest defines the request to delete a session\n149: type DeleteSessionRequest struct {\n150:     SessionID string `uri:\"sessionId\" binding:\"required\"`\n151: }\n152: \n153: // DeleteSessionResponse defines the response for session deletion\n154: type DeleteSessionResponse struct {\n155:     SessionID string    `json:\"sessionId\"`\n156:     DeletedAt time.Time `json:\"deletedAt\"`\n157: }\n158: \n159: // ErrorResponse defines the error response structure\n160: type ErrorResponse struct {\n161:     Error string `json:\"error\"`\n162:     Code  string `json:\"code,omitempty\"`\n163: }\n164: \n165: // EntryPoint defines a sandbox entry point\n166: type EntryPoint struct {\n167:     Protocol string `json:\"protocol\"`\n168:     Endpoint string `json:\"endpoint\"`\n169:     Path     string `json:\"path,omitempty\"`\n170:     Port     int32  `json:\"port,omitempty\"`\n171: }\n172: \n173: // SandboxInfo contains sandbox metadata and connection details\n174: type SandboxInfo struct {\n175:     SandboxID    string        `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n176:     SandboxName  string        `json:\"sandboxName\"`\n177:     SessionID    string        `json:\"sessionId\"`\n178:     Kind         string        `json:\"kind\"`\n179:     Namespace    string        `json:\"namespace\"`\n180:     Name         string        `json:\"name\"`\n181:     EntryPoints  []EntryPoint  `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n182:     PodIP        string        `json:\"podIP,omitempty\"`\n183:     NodeName     string        `json:\"nodeName,omitempty\"`\n184:     CreatedAt    time.Time     `json:\"createdAt\"`\n185:     ExpiresAt    time.Time     `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n186:     LastActivity time.Time     `json:\"lastActivity\"`\n187: }\n188: ```\n189: \n190: ### Controller Types\n191: \n192: **File**: `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/sandbox_manager.go`\n193: \n194: ```go\n195: // SandboxManager manages sandbox lifecycle\n196: type SandboxManager struct {\n197:     k8sClient    kubernetes.Interface\n198:     runtimeClient runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n199:     sandboxClient agentv1.SandboxInterface\n200:     store        store.Store\n201:     jwtManager   *auth.JWTManager\n202:     config       *Config\n203: }\n204: \n205: // SessionMetadata contains session metadata stored in Redis\n206: type SessionMetadata struct {\n207:     SessionID    string    `json:\"sessionId\"`\n208:     SandboxID    string    `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n209:     SandboxName  string    `json:\"sandboxName\"`\n210:     Kind         string    `json:\"kind\"`\n211:     Namespace    string    `json:\"namespace\"`\n212:     Name         string    `json:\"name\"`\n213:     EntryPoints  []string  `json:\"entryPoints\"` // JSON serialized EntryPoints\n214:     PodIP        string    `json:\"podIP,omitempty\"`\n215:     NodeName     string    `json:\"nodeName,omitempty\"`\n216:     CreatedAt    time.Time `json:\"createdAt\"`\n217:     ExpiresAt    time.Time `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n218:     LastActivity time.Time `json:\"lastActivity\"`\n219: }\n220: \n221: // SessionConfig contains session configuration\n222: type SessionConfig struct {\n223:     Timeout         time.Duration\n224:     MaxDuration     time.Duration\n225:     KeepAlive       bool\n226:     RenewalWindow   time.Duration\n227: }\n228: ```\n229: \n230: ### Configuration Types\n231: \n232: **File**: `pkg/workloadmanager/config/config.go`\n233: \n234: ```go\n235: // Config contains WorkloadManager configuration\n236: type Config struct {\n237:     Server   ServerConfig   `json:\"server\"`\n238:     Redis    RedisConfig    `json:\"redis\"`\n239:     K8s      K8sConfig      `json:\"k8s\"`\n240:     Auth     AuthConfig     `json:\"auth\"`\n241:     Session  SessionConfig  `json:\"session\"`\n242:     Metrics  MetricsConfig  `json:\"metrics\"`\n243: }\n244: \n245: // ServerConfig contains HTTP server configuration\n246: type ServerConfig struct {\n247:     Port                string        `json:\"port\"`\n248:     Host                string        `json:\"host\"`\n249:     ReadTimeout         time.Duration `json:\"readTimeout\"`\n250:     WriteTimeout        time.Duration `json:\"writeTimeout\"`\n251:     IdleTimeout         time.Duration `json:\"idleTimeout\"`\n252:     ShutdownTimeout     time.Duration `json:\"shutdownTimeout\"`\n253:     EnableProfiling     bool          `json:\"enableProfiling\"`\n254:     EnablePprof         bool          `json:\"enablePprof\"`\n255:     MaxHeaderBytes      int           `json:\"maxHeaderBytes\"`\n256:     EnableTLS           bool          `json:\"enableTLS\"`\n257:     TLSCertFile         string        `json:\"tlsCertFile\"`\n258:     TLSKeyFile          string        `json:\"tlsKeyFile\"`\n259: }\n260: \n261: // RedisConfig contains Redis connection configuration\n262: type RedisConfig struct {\n263:     Addr         string        `json:\"addr\"`\n264:     Password     string        `json:\"password\"`\n265:     DB           int           `json:\"db\"`\n266:     PoolSize     int           `json:\"poolSize\"`\n267:     MinIdleConns int           `json:\"minIdleConns\"`\n268:     MaxRetries   int           `json:\"maxRetries\"`\n269:     DialTimeout  time.Duration `json:\"dialTimeout\"`\n270:     ReadTimeout  time.Duration `json:\"readTimeout\"`\n271:     WriteTimeout time.Duration `json:\"writeTimeout\"`\n272:     PoolTimeout  time.Duration `json:\"poolTimeout\"`\n273:     IdleTimeout  time.Duration `json:\"idleTimeout\"`\n274: }\n275: \n276: // K8sConfig contains Kubernetes client configuration\n277: type K8sConfig struct {\n278:     QPS             float64       `json:\"qps\"`\n279:     Burst           int           `json:\"burst\"`\n280:     Timeout         time.Duration `json:\"timeout\"`\n281:     InClusterConfig bool          `json:\"inClusterConfig\"`\n282:     Kubeconfig      string        `json:\"kubeconfig\"`\n283: }\n284: \n285: // AuthConfig contains authentication configuration\n286: type AuthConfig struct {\n287:     EnableAuth          bool          `json:\"enableAuth\"`\n288:     JWTSigningMethod    string        `json:\"jwtSigningMethod\"`\n289:     JWTExpiration       time.Duration `json:\"jwtExpiration\"`\n290:     RSAPrivateKeyPath   string        `json:\"rsaPrivateKeyPath\"`\n291:     RSAPublicKeyPath    string        `json:\"rsaPublicKeyPath\"`\n292:     EnableK8sTokenReview bool         `json:\"enableK8sTokenReview\"`\n293:     K8sAPIAudience      string        `json:\"k8sAPIAudience\"`\n294: }\n295: \n296: // SessionConfig contains session management configuration\n297: type SessionConfig struct {\n298:     DefaultTimeout     time.Duration `json:\"defaultTimeout\"`\n299:     MaxDuration        time.Duration `json:\"maxDuration\"`\n300:     CleanupInterval    time.Duration `json:\"cleanupInterval\"`\n301:     KeepAliveEnabled   bool          `json:\"keepAliveEnabled\"`\n302:     KeepAliveInterval  time.Duration `json:\"keepAliveInterval\"`\n303:     RenewalWindow      time.Duration `json:\"renewalWindow\"`\n304: }\n305: \n306: // MetricsConfig contains metrics configuration\n307: type MetricsConfig struct {\n308:     Enabled        bool          `json:\"enabled\"`\n309:     Port           string        `json:\"port\"`\n310:     Path           string        `json:\"path\"`\n311:     EnableRuntime  bool          `json:\"enableRuntime\"`\n312:     EnableProcess  bool          `json:\"enableProcess\"`\n313:     RuntimeInterval time.Duration `json:\"runtimeInterval\"`\n314: }\n315: ```\n316: \n317: ## API Contracts\n318: \n319: ### HTTP API Endpoints\n320: \n321: #### Create Sandbox\n322: \n323: **POST** `/v1/agent-runtime` or `/v1/code-interpreter`\n324: \n325: **Request Headers**:\n326: ```\n327: Content-Type: application/json\n328: Authorization: Bearer <service-account-token> (optional, when EnableK8sTokenReview is true)\n329: ```\n330: \n331: **Request Body**:\n332: ```json\n333: {\n334:   \"kind\": \"AgentRuntime|CodeInterpreter\",\n335:   \"name\": \"python-runtime\",\n336:   \"namespace\": \"agentcube\"\n337: }\n338: ```\n339: \n340: **Success Response** (200 OK):\n341: ```json\n342: {\n343:   \"sessionId\": \"uuid-v4\",\n344:   \"sandboxId\": \"sandbox-uuid\",\n345:   \"sandboxName\": \"python-runtime-xxxxx\",\n346:   \"entryPoints\": [\n347:     {\n348:       \"protocol\": \"http\",\n349:       \"endpoint\": \"10.244.1.5:8080\",\n350:       \"path\": \"/\",\n351:       \"port\": 8080\n352:     }\n353:   ],\n354:   \"createdAt\": \"2024-01-01T00:00:00Z\",\n355:   \"expiresAt\": \"2024-01-01T01:00:00Z\"\n356: }\n357: ```\n358: \n359: **Error Responses**:\n360: - 400 Bad Request: Invalid request parameters\n361: - 401 Unauthorized: Invalid or missing authentication\n362: - 403 Forbidden: Insufficient permissions\n363: - 404 Not Found: AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter not found\n364: - 429 Too Many Requests: Rate limit exceeded\n365: - 500 Internal Server Error: Server error\n366: \n367: ```json\n368: {\n369:   \"error\": \"AgentRuntime 'python-runtime' not found in namespace 'agentcube'\",\n370:   \"code\": \"SANDBOX_TEMPLATE_NOT_FOUND\"\n371: }\n372: ```\n373: \n374: #### Get Session\n375: \n376: **GET** `/v1/sessions/:sessionId`\n377: \n378: **Request Headers**:\n379: ```\n380: Authorization: Bearer <service-account-token> (optional)\n381: ```\n382: \n383: **Success Response** (200 OK):\n384: ```json\n385: {\n386:   \"sessionId\": \"uuid-v4\",\n387:   \"sandboxId\": \"sandbox-uuid\",\n388:   \"sandboxName\": \"python-runtime-xxxxx\",\n389:   \"kind\": \"AgentRuntime\",\n390:   \"namespace\": \"agentcube\",\n391:   \"name\": \"python-runtime\",\n392:   \"entryPoints\": [\n393:     {\n394:       \"protocol\": \"http\",\n395:       \"endpoint\": \"10.244.1.5:8080\",\n396:       \"path\": \"/\",\n397:       \"port\": 8080\n398:     }\n399:   ],\n400:   \"lastActivity\": \"2024-01-01T00:30:00Z\",\n401:   \"createdAt\": \"2024-01-01T00:00:00Z\",\n402:   \"expiresAt\": \"2024-01-01T01:00:00Z\"\n403: }\n404: ```\n405: \n406: **Error Responses**:\n407: - 404 Not Found: Session not found or expired\n408: \n409: ```json\n410: {\n411:   \"error\": \"Session 'uuid-v4' not found\",\n412:   \"code\": \"SESSION_NOT_FOUND\"\n413: }\n414: ```\n415: \n416: #### Delete Session\n417: \n418: **DELETE** `/v1/sessions/:sessionId`\n419: \n420: **Request Headers**:\n421: ```\n422: Authorization: Bearer <service-account-token> (optional)\n423: ```\n424: \n425: **Success Response** (200 OK):\n426: ```json\n427: {\n428:   \"sessionId\": \"uuid-v4\",\n429:   \"deletedAt\": \"2024-01-01T00:45:00Z\"\n430: }\n431: ```\n432: \n433: #### Health Endpoints\n434: \n435: **GET** `/health/live`\n436: ```\n437: Status: 200 OK\n438: Body: {\"status\":\"alive\"}\n439: ```\n440: \n441: **GET** `/health/ready`\n442: ```\n443: Status: 200 OK\n444: Body: {\"status\":\"ready\"}\n445: ```\n446: \n447: **GET** `/health/ready` (when not ready)\n448: ```\n449: Status: 503 Service Unavailable\n450: Body: {\n451:   \"status\": \"not ready\",\n452:   \"error\": \"redis connection failed\"\n453: }\n454: ```\n455: \n456: ### Storage Interface\n457: \n458: **File**: `pkg/workloadmanager/storage/session_store.go`\n459: \n460: ```go\n461: // SessionStore defines the session storage interface\n462: type SessionStore interface {\n463:     // CreateSession creates a new session record\n464:     CreateSession(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, metadata *SessionMetadata, ttl time.Duration) error\n465:     \n466:     // GetSession retrieves session metadata by session ID\n467:     GetSession(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*SessionMetadata, error)\n468:     \n469:     // UpdateSessionActivity updates the last activity timestamp\n470:     UpdateSessionActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, timestamp time.Time) error\n471:     \n472:     // DeleteSession removes a session record\n473:     DeleteSession(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n474:     \n475:     // ExtendSession extends the session expiration\n476:     ExtendSession(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, ttl time.Duration) error\n477:     \n478:     // ListSessions lists all active sessions (for admin/debug)\n479:     ListSessions(ctx context.Context, kind, namespace, name string) ([]*SessionMetadata, error)\n480:     \n481:     // GetSessionCount returns the count of active sessions\n482:     GetSessionCount(ctx context.Context) (int64, error)\n483: }\n484: ```\n485: \n486: ### Kubernetes Client Interface\n487: \n488: **File**: `pkg/workloadmanager/client/k8s_client.go`\n489: \n490: ```go\n491: // K8sClient wraps Kubernetes client operations\n492: type K8sClient struct {\n493:     clientset     kubernetes.Interface\n494:     runtimeClient runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n495:     sandboxClient agentv1.SandboxInterface\n496:     config        *rest.Config\n497: }\n498: \n499: // CreateSandboxPod creates a sandbox pod from AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter spec\n500: func (c *K8sClient) CreateSandboxPod(ctx context.Context, kind, namespace, name string) (*SandboxPod, error)\n501: \n502: // GetSandboxPod retrieves a sandbox pod by name\n503: func (c *K8sClient) GetSandboxPod(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string) (*SandboxPod, error)\n504: \n505: // DeleteSandboxPod deletes a sandbox pod\n506: func (c *K8sClient) DeleteSandboxPod(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string) error\n507: \n508: // GetAgentRuntime retrieves an AgentRuntime CRD\n509: func (c *K8sClient) GetAgentRuntime(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n510: \n511: // GetCodeInterpreter retrieves a CodeInterpreter CRD\n512: func (c *K8sClient) GetCodeInterpreter(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n513: \n514: // WatchSandboxPods watches sandbox pods for changes\n515: func (c *K8sClient) WatchSandboxPods(ctx context.Context, namespace string) (<-chan watch.Event, error)\n516: ```\n517: \n518: ## Error Handling\n519: \n520: ### Error Types\n521: \n522: **File**: `pkg/workloadmanager/api/errors.go`\n523: \n524: ```go\n525: // Common error codes\n526: const (\n527:     ErrorCodeBadRequest                = \"BAD_REQUEST\"\n528:     ErrorCodeUnauthorized              = \"UNAUTHORIZED\"\n529:     ErrorCodeForbidden                 = \"FORBIDDEN\"\n530:     ErrorCodeNotFound                  = \"NOT_FOUND\"\n531:     ErrorCodeSandboxTemplateNotFound   = \"SANDBOX_TEMPLATE_NOT_FOUND\"\n532:     ErrorCodeSessionNotFound           = \"SESSION_NOT_FOUND\"\n533:     ErrorCodeSessionExpired            = \"SESSION_EXPIRED\"\n534:     ErrorCodeSessionLimitExceeded      = \"SESSION_LIMIT_EXCEEDED\"\n535:     ErrorCodeRateLimitExceeded         = \"RATE_LIMIT_EXCEEDED\"\n536:     ErrorCodeInternalServerError       = \"INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR\"\n537:     ErrorCodeServiceUnavailable        = \"SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE\"\n538:     ErrorCodeRedisConnectionFailed     = \"REDIS_CONNECTION_FAILED\"\n539:     ErrorCodeK8sConnectionFailed       = \"K8S_CONNECTION_FAILED\"\n540:     ErrorCodeJWTSigningFailed          = \"JWT_SIGNING_FAILED\"\n541:     ErrorCodePodCreationFailed         = \"POD_CREATION_FAILED\"\n542: )\n543: \n544: // WorkloadManagerError defines the WorkloadManager error type\n545: type WorkloadManagerError struct {\n546:     Code    string `json:\"code\"`\n547:     Message string `json:\"message\"`\n548:     Cause   error  `json:\"-\"`\n549: }\n550: \n551: // Error implements the error interface\n552: func (e *WorkloadManagerError) Error() string {\n553:     if e.Cause != nil {\n554:         return fmt.Sprintf(\"%s: %s (caused by: %v)\", e.Code, e.Message, e.Cause)\n555:     }\n556:     return fmt.Sprintf(\"%s: %s\", e.Code, e.Message)\n557: }\n558: \n559: // Unwrap returns the underlying error\n560: func (e *WorkloadManagerError) Unwrap() error {\n561:     return e.Cause\n562: }\n563: \n564: // Error constructors\n565: func NewBadRequestError(message string, cause error) *WorkloadManagerError\n566: func NewUnauthorizedError(message string, cause error) *WorkloadManagerError\n567: func NewForbiddenError(message string, cause error) *WorkloadManagerError\n568: func NewNotFoundError(resource, identifier string) *WorkloadManagerError\n569: func NewSandboxTemplateNotFoundError(namespace, name, kind string) *WorkloadManagerError\n570: func NewSessionNotFoundError(sessionID string) *WorkloadManagerError\n571: func NewSessionExpiredError(sessionID string) *WorkloadManagerError\n572: func NewSessionLimitExceededError(limit int) *WorkloadManagerError\n573: func NewRateLimitExceededError(message string) *WorkloadManagerError\n574: func NewInternalServerError(message string, cause error) *WorkloadManagerError\n575: func NewServiceUnavailableError(message string, cause error) *WorkloadManagerError\n576: ```\n577: \n578: ### Error Response Mapping\n579: \n580: | HTTP Status | Error Code | Condition |\n581: |-------------|------------|-----------|\n582: | 400 | BAD_REQUEST | Invalid request parameters |\n583: | 401 | UNAUTHORIZED | Invalid or missing authentication |\n584: | 403 | FORBIDDEN | Insufficient RBAC permissions |\n585: | 404 | SANDBOX_TEMPLATE_NOT_FOUND | AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter not found |\n586: | 404 | SESSION_NOT_FOUND | Session ID not in store |\n587: | 404 | SESSION_EXPIRED | Session TTL expired |\n588: | 429 | SESSION_LIMIT_EXCEEDED | Max sessions per runtime reached |\n589: | 429 | RATE_LIMIT_EXCEEDED | Rate limit exceeded |\n590: | 500 | POD_CREATION_FAILED | Failed to create sandbox pod |\n591: | 500 | JWT_SIGNING_FAILED | Failed to sign JWT |\n592: | 500 | INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR | Unexpected server error |\n593: | 503 | REDIS_CONNECTION_FAILED | Redis connection failed |\n594: | 503 | K8S_CONNECTION_FAILED | Kubernetes API connection failed |\n595: | 503 | SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE | Service not ready |\n596: \n597: ### Middleware Error Handling\n598: \n599: ```go\n600: // Recovery middleware recovers from panics\n601: func RecoveryMiddleware() gin.HandlerFunc {\n602:     return func(c *gin.Context) {\n603:         defer func() {\n604:             if err := recover(); err != nil {\n605:                 klog.Errorf(\"Panic recovered: %v\", err)\n606:                 c.JSON(500, ErrorResponse{\n607:                     Error: \"internal server error\",\n608:                     Code:  ErrorCodeInternalServerError,\n609:                 })\n610:                 c.Abort()\n611:             }\n612:         }()\n613:         c.Next()\n614:     }\n615: }\n616: \n617: // Error handling in handlers\n618: func handleError(c *gin.Context, err error) {\n619:     if wmErr, ok := err.(*WorkloadManagerError); ok {\n620:         statusCode := getHTTPStatusForErrorCode(wmErr.Code)\n621:         c.JSON(statusCode, ErrorResponse{\n622:             Error: wmErr.Message,\n623:             Code:  wmErr.Code,\n624:         })\n625:         return\n626:     }\n627:     \n628:     // Handle Kubernetes API errors\n629:     if apierrors.IsNotFound(err) {\n630:         c.JSON(404, ErrorResponse{\n631:             Error: \"resource not found\",\n632:             Code:  ErrorCodeNotFound,\n633:         })\n634:         return\n635:     }\n636:     \n637:     if apierrors.IsForbidden(err) {\n638:         c.JSON(403, ErrorResponse{\n639:             Error: \"access forbidden\",\n640:             Code:  ErrorCodeForbidden,\n641:         })\n642:         return\n643:     }\n644:     \n645:     // Default to internal server error\n646:     klog.Errorf(\"Unexpected error: %v\", err)\n647:     c.JSON(500, ErrorResponse{\n648:         Error: \"internal server error\",\n649:         Code:  ErrorCodeInternalServerError,\n650:     })\n651: }\n652: ```\n653: \n654: ## Testing Strategy\n655: \n656: ### Unit Tests\n657: \n658: **File**: `pkg/workloadmanager/api/handlers_test.go`\n659: \n660: ```go\n661: package api_test\n662: \n663: import (\n664:     \"context\"\n665:     \"net/http\"\n666:     \"net/http/httptest\"\n667:     \"testing\"\n668:     \"time\"\n669: \n670:     . \"github.com/onsi/ginkgo/v2\"\n671:     . \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"\n672:     \"github.com/gin-gonic/gin\"\n673:     \n674:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/api\"\n675:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/controller\"\n676:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/store\"\n677: )\n678: \n679: var _ = Describe(\"API Handlers\", func() {\n680:     var (\n681:         router      *gin.Engine\n682:         mockCtrl    *controller.MockSandboxManager\n683:         mockStore   *store.MockSessionStore\n684:         authManager *auth.MockAuthManager\n685:     )\n686: \n687:     BeforeEach(func() {\n688:         gin.SetMode(gin.TestMode)\n689:         router = gin.New()\n690:         mockCtrl = controller.NewMockSandboxManager()\n691:         mockStore = store.NewMockSessionStore()\n692:         authManager = auth.NewMockAuthManager()\n693:         \n694:         api.RegisterRoutes(router, mockCtrl, mockStore, authManager)\n695:     })\n696: \n697:     Describe(\"POST /v1/agent-runtime\", func() {\n698:         Context(\"Valid request\", func() {\n699:             It(\"should create sandbox and return session info\", func() {\n700:                 mockCtrl.EXPECT().CreateSandbox(\n701:                     context.Background(),\n702:                     \"AgentRuntime\",\n703:                     \"default\",\n704:                     \"python-runtime\",\n705:                 ).Return(&controller.SandboxInfo{\n706:                     SessionID:    \"test-session-id\",\n707:                     SandboxID:    \"test-sandbox-id\",\n708:                     SandboxName:  \"python-runtime-abcde\",\n709:                     EntryPoints:  []api.EntryPoint{...},\n710:                     CreatedAt:    time.Now(),\n711:                     ExpiresAt:    time.Now().Add(time.Hour),\n712:                 }, nil)\n713: \n714:                 reqBody := `{\"kind\":\"AgentRuntime\",\"name\":\"python-runtime\",\"namespace\":\"default\"}`\n715:                 req := httptest.NewRequest(\"POST\", \"/v1/agent-runtime\", strings.NewReader(reqBody))\n716:                 req.Header.Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n717:                 resp := httptest.NewRecorder()\n718: \n719:                 router.ServeHTTP(resp, req)\n720: \n721:                 Expect(resp.Code).To(Equal(http.StatusOK))\n722:                 var respBody api.CreateSandboxResponse\n723:                 json.Unmarshal(resp.Body.Bytes(), &respBody)\n724:                 Expect(respBody.SessionID).To(Equal(\"test-session-id\"))\n725:             })\n726:         })\n727: \n728:         Context(\"Invalid kind\", func() {\n729:             It(\"should return 400 Bad Request\", func() {\n730:                 reqBody := `{\"kind\":\"InvalidKind\",\"name\":\"python-runtime\",\"namespace\":\"default\"}`\n731:                 req := httptest.NewRequest(\"POST\", \"/v1/agent-runtime\", strings.NewReader(reqBody))\n732:                 req.Header.Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n733:                 resp := httptest.NewRecorder()\n734: \n735:                 router.ServeHTTP(resp, req)\n736: \n737:                 Expect(resp.Code).To(Equal(http.StatusBadRequest))\n738:             })\n739:         })\n740: \n741:         Context(\"AgentRuntime not found\", func() {\n742:             It(\"should return 404 Not Found\", func() {\n743:                 mockCtrl.EXPECT().CreateSandbox(\n744:                     context.Background(),\n745:                     \"AgentRuntime\",\n746:                     \"default\",\n747:                     \"nonexistent\",\n748:                 ).Return(nil, api.NewSandboxTemplateNotFoundError(\"default\", \"nonexistent\", \"AgentRuntime\"))\n749: \n750:                 reqBody := `{\"kind\":\"AgentRuntime\",\"name\":\"nonexistent\",\"namespace\":\"default\"}`\n751:                 req := httptest.NewRequest(\"POST\", \"/v1/agent-runtime\", strings.NewReader(reqBody))\n752:                 req.Header.Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n753:                 resp := httptest.NewRecorder()\n754: \n755:                 router.ServeHTTP(resp, req)\n756: \n757:                 Expect(resp.Code).To(Equal(http.StatusNotFound))\n758:                 var respBody api.ErrorResponse\n759:                 json.Unmarshal(resp.Body.Bytes(), &respBody)\n760:                 Expect(respBody.Code).To(Equal(\"SANDBOX_TEMPLATE_NOT_FOUND\"))\n761:             })\n762:         })\n763:     })\n764: \n765:     Describe(\"GET /v1/sessions/:sessionId\", func() {\n766:         Context(\"Session exists\", func() {\n767:             It(\"should return session info\", func() {\n768:                 mockStore.EXPECT().GetSession(\n769:                     context.Background(),\n770:                     \"test-session-id\",\n771:                 ).Return(&store.SessionMetadata{\n772:                     SessionID:    \"test-session-id\",\n773:                     SandboxID:    \"test-sandbox-id\",\n774:                     SandboxName:  \"python-runtime-abcde\",\n775:                     Kind:         \"AgentRuntime\",\n776:                     CreatedAt:    time.Now(),\n777:                     ExpiresAt:    time.Now().Add(time.Hour),\n778:                     LastActivity: time.Now(),\n779:                 }, nil)\n780: \n781:                 req := httptest.NewRequest(\"GET\", \"/v1/sessions/test-session-id\", nil)\n782:                 resp := httptest.NewRecorder()\n783: \n784:                 router.ServeHTTP(resp, req)\n785: \n786:                 Expect(resp.Code).To(Equal(http.StatusOK))\n787:                 var respBody api.GetSessionResponse\n788:                 json.Unmarshal(resp.Body.Bytes(), &respBody)\n789:                 Expect(respBody.SessionID).To(Equal(\"test-session-id\"))\n790:             })\n791:         })\n792: \n793:         Context(\"Session not found\", func() {\n794:             It(\"should return 404 Not Found\", func() {\n795:                 mockStore.EXPECT().GetSession(\n796:                     context.Background(),\n797:                     \"nonexistent-session\",\n798:                 ).Return(nil, store.ErrNotFound)\n799: \n800:                 req := httptest.NewRequest(\"GET\", \"/v1/sessions/nonexistent-session\", nil)\n801:                 resp := httptest.NewRecorder()\n802: \n803:                 router.ServeHTTP(resp, req)\n804: \n805:                 Expect(resp.Code).To(Equal(http.StatusNotFound))\n806:                 var respBody api.ErrorResponse\n807:                 json.Unmarshal(resp.Body.Bytes(), &respBody)\n808:                 Expect(respBody.Code).To(Equal(\"SESSION_NOT_FOUND\"))\n809:             })\n810:         })\n811:     })\n812: })\n813: ```\n814: \n815: ### Integration Tests\n816: \n817: **File**: `pkg/workloadmanager/integration_test.go`\n818: \n819: ```go\n820: package workloadmanager_test\n821: \n822: import (\n823:     \"context\"\n824:     \"testing\"\n825:     \"time\"\n826: \n827:     . \"github.com/onsi/ginkgo/v2\"\n828:     . \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"\n829:     metav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n830:     \"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes/scheme\"\n831:     \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/client\"\n832:     \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/envtest\"\n833: \n834:     runtimev1alpha1 \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n835:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager\"\n836: )\n837: \n838: var (\n839:     envTest   *envtest.Environment\n840:     k8sClient client.Client\n841:     wm        *workloadmanager.WorkloadManager\n842: )\n843: \n844: var _ = BeforeSuite(func() {\n845:     err := runtimev1alpha1.AddToScheme(scheme.Scheme)\n846:     Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n847: \n848:     envTest = &envtest.Environment{\n849:         CRDDirectoryPaths: []string{\"../../manifests/charts/base/crds\"},\n850:     }\n851: \n852:     cfg, err := envTest.Start()\n853:     Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n854: \n855:     k8sClient, err = client.New(cfg, client.Options{Scheme: scheme.Scheme})\n856:     Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n857: })\n858: \n859: var _ = AfterSuite(func() {\n860:     err := envTest.Stop()\n861:     Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n862: })\n863: \n864: var _ = Describe(\"WorkloadManager Integration\", func() {\n865:     Context(\"Sandbox lifecycle\", func() {\n866:         It(\"should create sandbox from AgentRuntime\", func(ctx SpecContext) {\n867:             namespace := \"default\"\n868:             \n869:             art := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n870:                 ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n871:                     Name:      \"python-runtime\",\n872:                     Namespace: namespace,\n873:                 },\n874:                 Spec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n875:                     SessionTimeout:     &metav1.Duration{Duration: 15 * time.Minute},\n876:                     MaxSessionDuration: &metav1.Duration{Duration: 8 * time.Hour},\n877:                     PodTemplate: &runtimev1alpha1.SandboxTemplate{\n878:                         Spec: runtimev1alpha1.SandboxPodSpec{\n879:                             Containers: []runtimev1alpha1.SandboxContainer{\n880:                                 {\n881:                                     Name:  \"agent\",\n882:                                     Image: \"python:3.11-slim\",\n883:                                 },\n884:                             },\n885:                         },\n886:                     },\n887:                 },\n888:             }\n889: \n890:             err := k8sClient.Create(ctx, art)\n891:             Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n892: \n893:             resp, err := wm.CreateSandbox(ctx, &workloadmanager.CreateSandboxRequest{\n894:                 Kind:      \"AgentRuntime\",\n895:                 Name:      \"python-runtime\",\n896:                 Namespace: namespace,\n897:             })\n898:             Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n899:             Expect(resp.SessionID).NotTo(BeEmpty())\n900:             Expect(resp.SandboxName).NotTo(BeEmpty())\n901:         }, SpecTimeout(30*time.Second))\n902: \n903:         It(\"should cleanup expired sessions\", func(ctx SpecContext) {\n904:             sessionID := \"test-expired-session\"\n905:             \n906:             err := wm.CreateSessionRecord(ctx, sessionID, &workloadmanager.SandboxInfo{\n907:                 SessionID:    sessionID,\n908:                 SandboxID:    \"sandbox-id\",\n909:                 SandboxName:  \"test-sandbox\",\n910:                 ExpiresAt:    time.Now().Add(-1 * time.Hour),\n911:             })\n912:             Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n913: \n914:             Eventually(func() bool {\n915:                 _, err := wm.GetSession(ctx, sessionID)\n916:                 return err == nil\n917:             }, 10*time.Second, time.Second).Should(BeFalse())\n918:         }, SpecTimeout(30*time.Second))\n919:     })\n920: })\n921: ```\n922: \n923: ### E2E Tests\n924: \n925: **File**: `test/e2e/workloadmanager_test.go`\n926: \n927: ```go\n928: package e2e\n929: \n930: import (\n931:     \"context\"\n932:     \"testing\"\n933:     \"time\"\n934: \n935:     . \"github.com/onsi/ginkgo/v2\"\n936:     . \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"\n937:     metav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n938: \n939:     runtimev1alpha1 \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n940:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/test/e2e/framework\"\n941: )\n942: \n943: var _ = Describe(\"WorkloadManager E2E\", func() {\n944:     f := framework.NewDefaultFramework(\"workloadmanager\")\n945: \n946:     Context(\"Create and manage sandboxes\", func() {\n947:         It(\"should create sandbox from AgentRuntime and route traffic\", func() {\n948:             ctx := context.Background()\n949:             \n950:             art := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n951:                 ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n952:                     Name:      \"e2e-python-runtime\",\n953:                     Namespace: f.Namespace.Name,\n954:                 },\n955:                 Spec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n956:                     SessionTimeout:     &metav1.Duration{Duration: 5 * time.Minute},\n957:                     MaxSessionDuration: &metav1.Duration{Duration: 1 * time.Hour},\n958:                     PodTemplate: &runtimev1alpha1.SandboxTemplate{\n959:                         Spec: runtimev1alpha1.SandboxPodSpec{\n960:                             Containers: []runtimev1alpha1.SandboxContainer{\n961:                                 {\n962:                                     Name:  \"agent\",\n963:                                     Image: \"ghcr.io/volcano-sh/python-agent:latest\",\n964:                                     Ports: []runtimev1alpha1.SandboxContainerPort{\n965:                                         {ContainerPort: 8080},\n966:                                     },\n967:                                 },\n968:                             },\n969:                         },\n970:                     },\n971:                 },\n972:             }\n973: \n974:             err := f.Client.Create(ctx, art)\n975:             Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n976: \n977:             // Create sandbox via WorkloadManager API\n978:             resp, err := f.WMClient.CreateSandbox(ctx, &CreateSandboxRequest{\n979:                 Kind:      \"AgentRuntime\",\n980:                 Name:      \"e2e-python-runtime\",\n981:                 Namespace: f.Namespace.Name,\n982:             })\n983:             Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n984: \n985:             // Verify sandbox pod is created\n986:             Eventually(func() bool {\n987:                 pod, err := f.ClientSet.CoreV1().Pods(f.Namespace.Name).Get(\n988:                     ctx, resp.SandboxName, metav1.GetOptions{},\n989:                 )\n990:                 if err != nil {\n991:                     return false\n992:                 }\n993:                 return pod.Status.Phase == \"Running\"\n994:             }, 2*time.Minute, 5*time.Second).Should(BeTrue())\n995: \n996:             // Verify session is stored\n997:             session, err := f.WMClient.GetSession(ctx, resp.SessionID)\n998:             Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n999:             Expect(session.SessionID).To(Equal(resp.SessionID))\n1000: \n1001:             // Test routing through router\n1002:             req := f.NewRequest(\"GET\", f.RouterURL+\"/v1/namespaces/\"+f.Namespace.Name+\"/agent-runtimes/e2e-python-runtime/invocations/test\", nil)\n1003:             req.Header.Set(\"x-agentcube-session-id\", resp.SessionID)\n1004:             \n1005:             httpResponse, err := f.HTTPClient.Do(req)\n1006:             Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n1007:             Expect(httpResponse.StatusCode).To(Equal(http.StatusOK))\n1008:         })\n1009:     })\n1010: })\n1011: ```\n1012: \n1013: ## Metrics and Observability\n1014: \n1015: ### Prometheus Metrics\n1016: \n1017: **File**: `pkg/workloadmanager/storage/metrics.go`\n1018: \n1019: ```go\n1020: const (\n1021:     // Session metrics\n1022:     metricSessionCount = \"workloadmanager_sessions_total\"\n1023:     metricSessionCreated = \"workloadmanager_sessions_created_total\"\n1024:     metricSessionDeleted = \"workloadmanager_sessions_deleted_total\"\n1025:     metricSessionExpired = \"workloadmanager_sessions_expired_total\"\n1026:     \n1027:     // Sandbox metrics\n1028:     metricSandboxCreated = \"workloadmanager_sandboxes_created_total\"\n1029:     metricSandboxFailed = \"workloadmanager_sandboxes_failed_total\"\n1030:     metricSandboxActive = \"workloadmanager_sandboxes_active\"\n1031:     \n1032:     // Request metrics\n1033:     metricRequestDuration = \"workloadmanager_request_duration_seconds\"\n1034:     metricRequestTotal = \"workloadmanager_requests_total\"\n1035:     metricRequestErrors = \"workloadmanager_request_errors_total\"\n1036:     \n1037:     // Storage metrics\n1038:     metricStorageLatency = \"workloadmanager_storage_latency_seconds\"\n1039:     metricStorageErrors = \"workloadmanager_storage_errors_total\"\n1040:     \n1041:     // Kubernetes metrics\n1042:     metricK8sAPILatency = \"workloadmanager_k8s_api_latency_seconds\"\n1043:     metricK8sAPIErrors = \"workloadmanager_k8s_api_errors_total\"\n1044: )\n1045: \n1046: var (\n1047:     sessionCount = prometheus.NewGaugeVec(\n1048:         prometheus.GaugeOpts{\n1049:             Name: metricSessionCount,\n1050:             Help: \"Total number of active sessions\",\n1051:         },\n1052:         []string{\"kind\", \"namespace\", \"name\"},\n1053:     )\n1054:     \n1055:     sessionCreated = prometheus.NewCounterVec(\n1056:         prometheus.CounterOpts{\n1057:             Name: metricSessionCreated,\n1058:             Help: \"Total number of sessions created\",\n1059:         },\n1060:         []string{\"kind\", \"namespace\", \"name\"},\n1061:     )\n1062:     \n1063:     sandboxCreated = prometheus.NewCounterVec(\n1064:         prometheus.CounterOpts{\n1065:             Name: metricSandboxCreated,\n1066:             Help: \"Total number of sandboxes created\",\n1067:         },\n1068:         []string{\"kind\", \"namespace\", \"name\"},\n1069:     )\n1070:     \n1071:     requestDuration = prometheus.NewHistogramVec(\n1072:         prometheus.HistogramOpts{\n1073:             Name:    metricRequestDuration,\n1074:             Help:    \"Request duration in seconds\",\n1075:             Buckets: prometheus.DefBuckets,\n1076:         },\n1077:         []string{\"method\", \"endpoint\", \"status\"},\n1078:     )\n1079: )\n1080: \n1081: func init() {\n1082:     prometheus.MustRegister(sessionCount)\n1083:     prometheus.MustRegister(sessionCreated)\n1084:     prometheus.MustRegister(sandboxCreated)\n1085:     prometheus.MustRegister(requestDuration)\n1086: }\n1087: ```\n1088: \n1089: ### Logging\n1090: \n1091: **File**: `pkg/workloadmanager/server/logging.go`\n1092: \n1093: ```go\n1094: // Structured logging configuration\n1095: type LoggingConfig struct {\n1096:     Level      string `json:\"level\"`\n1097:     Format     string `json:\"format\"` // json or text\n1098:     Output     string `json:\"output\"` // stdout, stderr, or file path\n1099:     MaxSize    int    `json:\"maxSize\"`\n1100:     MaxAge     int    `json:\"maxAge\"`\n1101:     MaxBackups int    `json:\"maxBackups\"`\n1102: }\n1103: \n1104: // Log fields for structured logging\n1105: const (\n1106:     LogFieldSessionID    = \"session_id\"\n1107:     LogFieldSandboxID    = \"sandbox_id\"\n1108:     LogFieldSandboxName  = \"sandbox_name\"\n1109:     LogFieldKind         = \"kind\"\n1110:     LogFieldNamespace    = \"namespace\"\n1111:     LogFieldName         = \"name\"\n1112:     LogFieldUserID       = \"user_id\"\n1113:     LogFieldMethod       = \"method\"\n1114:     LogFieldPath         = \"path\"\n1115:     LogFieldStatusCode   = \"status_code\"\n1116:     LogFieldDuration     = \"duration_ms\"\n1117:     LogFieldError        = \"error\"\n1118:     LogFieldErrorCode    = \"error_code\"\n1119: )\n1120: \n1121: // Log helper functions\n1122: func LogSessionCreated(ctx context.Context, sessionID, sandboxID, kind, namespace, name string) {\n1123:     klog.InfoS(\"Session created\",\n1124:         LogFieldSessionID, sessionID,\n1125:         LogFieldSandboxID, sandboxID,\n1126:         LogFieldKind, kind,\n1127:         LogFieldNamespace, namespace,\n1128:         LogFieldName, name,\n1129:     )\n1130: }\n1131: \n1132: func LogSessionDeleted(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) {\n1133:     klog.InfoS(\"Session deleted\",\n1134:         LogFieldSessionID, sessionID,\n1135:     )\n1136: }\n1137: \n1138: func LogRequest(ctx context.Context, method, path string, statusCode int, duration time.Duration) {\n1139:     klog.InfoS(\"Request completed\",\n1140:         LogFieldMethod, method,\n1141:         LogFieldPath, path,\n1142:         LogFieldStatusCode, statusCode,\n1143:         LogFieldDuration, duration.Milliseconds(),\n1144:     )\n1145: }\n1146: \n1147: func LogError(ctx context.Context, err error, fields ...interface{}) {\n1148:     if wmErr, ok := err.(*WorkloadManagerError); ok {\n1149:         klog.ErrorS(err, \"WorkloadManager error\",\n1150:             append(fields,\n1151:                 LogFieldErrorCode, wmErr.Code,\n1152:                 LogFieldError, wmErr.Message,\n1153:             )...,\n1154:         )\n1155:     } else {\n1156:         klog.ErrorS(err, \"Unexpected error\", fields...)\n1157:     }\n1158: }\n1159: ```\n1160: \n1161: ## Security\n1162: \n1163: ### Authentication\n1164: \n1165: **File**: `pkg/workloadmanager/auth/k8s_auth.go`\n1166: \n1167: ```go\n1168: // K8sAuthenticator validates Kubernetes service account tokens\n1169: type K8sAuthenticator struct {\n1170:     clientset  kubernetes.Interface\n1171:     audience   string\n1172: }\n1173: \n1174: // Authenticate validates a service account token using TokenReview API\n1175: func (a *K8sAuthenticator) Authenticate(ctx context.Context, token string) (*AuthenticationInfo, error) {\n1176:     tokenReview := &authenticationv1.TokenReview{\n1177:         Spec: authenticationv1.TokenReviewSpec{\n1178:             Token:     token,\n1179:             Audiences: []string{a.audience},\n1180:         },\n1181:     }\n1182: \n1183:     resp, err := a.clientset.AuthenticationV1().TokenReviews().Create(ctx, tokenReview, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n1184:     if err != nil {\n1185:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"token review failed: %w\", err)\n1186:     }\n1187: \n1188:     if !resp.Status.Authenticated {\n1189:         return nil, NewUnauthorizedError(\"token authentication failed\", nil)\n1190:     }\n1191: \n1192:     return &AuthenticationInfo{\n1193:         Username: resp.Status.User.Username,\n1194:         UID:      resp.Status.User.UID,\n1195:         Groups:   resp.Status.User.Groups,\n1196:         Extra:    resp.Status.User.Extra,\n1197:     }, nil\n1198: }\n1199: \n1200: // AuthenticationInfo contains authenticated user information\n1201: type AuthenticationInfo struct {\n1202:     Username string\n1203:     UID      string\n1204:     Groups   []string\n1205:     Extra    map[string]authenticationv1.ExtraValue\n1206: }\n1207: ```\n1208: \n1209: ### Authorization (RBAC)\n1210: \n1211: **File**: `pkg/workloadmanager/auth/rbac.go`\n1212: \n1213: ```go\n1214: // Authorizer enforces RBAC policies\n1215: type Authorizer struct {\n1216:     subjectAccessReviewClient authorizationv1.SubjectAccessReviewInterface\n1217: }\n1218: \n1219: // CanCreateSandbox checks if the user can create a sandbox for the given runtime\n1220: func (a *Authorizer) CanCreateSandbox(ctx context.Context, user, namespace, name string) (bool, error) {\n1221:     sar := &authorizationv1.SubjectAccessReview{\n1222:         Spec: authorizationv1.SubjectAccessReviewSpec{\n1223:             User:   user,\n1224:             ResourceAttributes: &authorizationv1.ResourceAttributes{\n1225:                 Group:     \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\",\n1226:                 Resource:  \"agentruntimes\",\n1227:                 Verb:      \"get\",\n1228:                 Namespace: namespace,\n1229:                 Name:      name,\n1230:             },\n1231:         },\n1232:     }\n1233: \n1234:     resp, err := a.subjectAccessReviewClient.Create(ctx, sar, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n1235:     if err != nil {\n1236:         return false, err\n1237:     }\n1238: \n1239:     return resp.Status.Allowed, nil\n1240: }\n1241: \n1242: // CanDeleteSession checks if the user can delete a session\n1243: func (a *Authorizer) CanDeleteSession(ctx context.Context, user, sessionID string) (bool, error) {\n1244:     // Sessions are stored in Redis, so we check if the user has permission\n1245:     // to manage sandboxes in the namespace associated with the session\n1246:     sar := &authorizationv1.SubjectAccessReview{\n1247:         Spec: authorizationv1.SubjectAccessReviewSpec{\n1248:             User: user,\n1249:             NonResourceAttributes: &authorizationv1.NonResourceAttributes{\n1250:                 Verb:     \"delete\",\n1251:                 Path:     fmt.Sprintf(\"/v1/sessions/%s\", sessionID),\n1252:             },\n1253:         },\n1254:     }\n1255: \n1256:     resp, err := a.subjectAccessReviewClient.Create(ctx, sar, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n1257:     if err != nil {\n1258:         return false, err\n1259:     }\n1260: \n1261:     return resp.Status.Allowed, nil\n1262: }\n1263: ```\n1264: \n1265: ### JWT Signing\n1266: \n1267: **File**: `pkg/workloadmanager/auth/jwt.go`\n1268: \n1269: ```go\n1270: // JWTManager handles JWT token generation and validation\n1271: type JWTManager struct {\n1272:     privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey\n1273:     publicKey  *rsa.PublicKey\n1274:     expiration time.Duration\n1275:     issuer     string\n1276: }\n1277: \n1278: // GenerateToken generates a JWT token for sandbox access\n1279: func (j *JWTManager) GenerateToken(claims map[string]interface{}) (string, error) {\n1280:     now := time.Now()\n1281:     \n1282:     standardClaims := jwt.MapClaims{\n1283:         \"exp\": now.Add(j.expiration).Unix(),\n1284:         \"iat\": now.Unix(),\n1285:         \"iss\": j.issuer,\n1286:     }\n1287:     \n1288:     // Merge custom claims\n1289:     for k, v := range claims {\n1290:         standardClaims[k] = v\n1291:     }\n1292:     \n1293:     token := jwt.NewWithClaims(jwt.SigningMethodRS256, standardClaims)\n1294:     \n1295:     tokenString, err := token.SignedString(j.privateKey)\n1296:     if err != nil {\n1297:         return \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"failed to sign token: %w\", err)\n1298:     }\n1299:     \n1300:     return tokenString, nil\n1301: }\n1302: \n1303: // ValidateToken validates a JWT token and returns the claims\n1304: func (j *JWTManager) ValidateToken(tokenString string) (jwt.MapClaims, error) {\n1305:     token, err := jwt.Parse(tokenString, func(token *jwt.Token) (interface{}, error) {\n1306:         if _, ok := token.Method.(*jwt.SigningMethodRSA); !ok {\n1307:             return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"unexpected signing method: %v\", token.Header[\"alg\"])\n1308:         }\n1309:         return j.publicKey, nil\n1310:     })\n1311:     \n1312:     if err != nil {\n1313:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to parse token: %w\", err)\n1314:     }\n1315:     \n1316:     if claims, ok := token.Claims.(jwt.MapClaims); ok && token.Valid {\n1317:         return claims, nil\n1318:     }\n1319:     \n1320:     return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"invalid token\")\n1321: }\n1322: ```\n1323: \n1324: ## Dependencies\n1325: \n1326: ### Go Module Dependencies\n1327: \n1328: ```go\n1329: module github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube\n1330: \n1331: go 1.24\n1332: \n1333: require (\n1334:     github.com/gin-gonic/gin v1.10.0\n1335:     github.com/redis/go-redis/v9 v9.7.0\n1336:     github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5 v5.2.1\n1337:     k8s.io/api v0.32.1\n1338:     k8s.io/apimachinery v0.32.1\n1339:     k8s.io/client-go v0.32.1\n1340:     sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime v0.19.2\n1341:     sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox v0.6.0\n1342:     github.com/prometheus/client_golang v1.20.5\n1343:     k8s.io/klog/v2 v2.130.1\n1344:     github.com/spf13/cobra v1.8.1\n1345:     github.com/spf13/viper v1.19.0\n1346: )\n1347: ```\n1348: \n1349: ### Environment Variables\n1350: \n1351: | Variable | Description | Default | Required |\n1352: |----------|-------------|---------|----------|\n1353: | `REDIS_ADDR` | Redis server address | `localhost:6379` | Yes |\n1354: | `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Redis password | empty | No |\n1355: | `REDIS_DB` | Redis database number | `0` | No |\n1356: | `KUBECONFIG` | Path to kubeconfig file | `~/.kube/config` | No (in-cluster) |\n1357: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_PORT` | HTTP server port | `8080` | No |\n1358: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_HOST` | HTTP server host | `0.0.0.0` | No |\n1359: | `ENABLE_TLS` | Enable TLS | `false` | No |\n1360: | `TLS_CERT_FILE` | TLS certificate file path | empty | No |\n1361: | `TLS_KEY_FILE` | TLS private key file path | empty | No |\n1362: | `JWT_EXPIRATION` | JWT token expiration duration | `5m` | No |\n1363: | `SESSION_TIMEOUT` | Default session timeout | `15m` | No |\n1364: | `MAX_SESSION_DURATION` | Maximum session duration | `8h` | No |\n1365: | `ENABLE_K8S_AUTH` | Enable Kubernetes token authentication | `true` | No |\n1366: | `K8S_API_AUDIENCE` | Kubernetes API audience for token review | `agentcube` | No |\n1367: | `METRICS_ENABLED` | Enable Prometheus metrics | `true` | No |\n1368: | `METRICS_PORT` | Metrics server port | `9090` | No |\n1369: | `LOG_LEVEL` | Logging level | `info` | No |\n1370: | `LOG_FORMAT` | Log format (json/text) | `json` | No |\n1371: \n1372: ### Kubernetes RBAC Permissions\n1373: \n1374: ```yaml\n1375: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n1376: kind: ClusterRole\n1377: metadata:\n1378:   name: workloadmanager\n1379: rules:\n1380:   # AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs\n1381:   - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n1382:     resources: [\"agentruntimes\", \"codeinterpreters\"]\n1383:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n1384:   \n1385:   # Sandbox resources\n1386:   - apiGroups: [\"agent-sandbox.volcano.sh\"]\n1387:     resources: [\"sandboxes\", \"sandboxclaims\"]\n1388:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"create\", \"update\", \"delete\", \"watch\"]\n1389:   \n1390:   # Pod management\n1391:   - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n1392:     resources: [\"pods\"]\n1393:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"create\", \"delete\", \"watch\"]\n1394:   \n1395:   # Secret management\n1396:   - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n1397:     resources: [\"secrets\"]\n1398:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"create\", \"delete\"]\n1399:   \n1400:   # Authentication\n1401:   - apiGroups: [\"authentication.k8s.io\"]\n1402:     resources: [\"tokenreviews\"]\n1403:     verbs: [\"create\"]\n1404:   \n1405:   # Authorization\n1406:   - apiGroups: [\"authorization.k8s.io\"]\n1407:     resources: [\"subjectaccessreviews\"]\n1408:     verbs: [\"create\"]\n1409:   \n1410:   # ConfigMaps and ConfigMap volume sources\n1411:   - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n1412:     resources: [\"configmaps\"]\n1413:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\"]\n1414: ```\n1415: \n1416: ## Integration Points\n1417: \n1418: ### With Router\n1419: \n1420: The Router calls the WorkloadManager HTTP API:\n1421: \n1422: ```\n1423: POST {WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL}/v1/agent-runtime\n1424: POST {WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL}/v1/code-interpreter\n1425: GET {WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL}/v1/sessions/{sessionID}\n1426: DELETE {WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL}/v1/sessions/{sessionID}\n1427: ```\n1428: \n1429: The WorkloadManager returns `CreateSandboxResponse` with session and sandbox information.\n1430: \n1431: ### With Session Store\n1432: \n1433: The WorkloadManager uses the Redis session store:\n1434: \n1435: ```go\n1436: store.Storage() // Returns shared store client\n1437: store.CreateSession(ctx, sessionID, metadata, ttl)\n1438: store.GetSession(ctx, sessionID)\n1439: store.UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID, timestamp)\n1440: store.DeleteSession(ctx, sessionID)\n1441: ```\n1442: \n1443: ### With Kubernetes API\n1444: \n1445: The WorkloadManager uses the generated client-go:\n1446: \n1447: ```go\n1448: runtimeClient := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1()\n1449: agentRuntime, err := runtimeClient.AgentRuntimes(namespace).Get(ctx, name, opts)\n1450: pod, err := k8sClient.CoreV1().Pods(namespace).Create(ctx, pod, opts)\n1451: ```\n1452: \n1453: ### With Sandbox API\n1454: \n1455: The WorkloadManager uses the agent-sandbox API:\n1456: \n1457: ```go\n1458: sandboxClient := agentv1.NewForConfig(config)\n1459: sandbox, err := sandboxClient.Sandboxes(namespace).Create(ctx, &sandbox, opts)\n1460: ```\n1461: \n1462: ## Documentation\n1463: \n1464: ### API Documentation\n1465: \n1466: OpenAPI/Swagger documentation should be generated and served at `/swagger` endpoint:\n1467: \n1468: ```go\n1469: import \"github.com/swaggo/gin-swagger\"\n1470: import \"github.com/swaggo/files\"\n1471: \n1472: // In router setup\n1473: r.GET(\"/swagger/*any\", ginSwagger.WrapHandler(swaggerFiles.Handler))\n1474: ```\n1475: \n1476: ### Configuration Reference\n1477: \n1478: All configuration options should be documented in `docs/configuration.md` with:\n1479: - Default values\n1480: - Environment variable names\n1481: - CLI flag names\n1482: - Description of each option\n1483: - Examples\n1484: \n1485: ### Examples\n1486: \n1487: **Example AgentRuntime** (`examples/agentruntime.yaml`):\n1488: \n1489: ```yaml\n1490: apiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\n1491: kind: AgentRuntime\n1492: metadata:\n1493:   name: python-agent\n1494:   namespace: agentcube\n1495: spec:\n1496:   sessionTimeout: \"15m\"\n1497:   maxSessionDuration: \"8h\"\n1498:   podTemplate:\n1499:     metadata:\n1500:       labels:\n1501:         app: python-agent\n1502:     spec:\n1503:       containers:\n1504:       - name: agent\n1505:         image: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/python-agent:latest\n1506:         ports:\n1507:         - containerPort: 8080\n1508:           protocol: TCP\n1509:         resources:\n1510:           limits:\n1511:             cpu: \"500m\"\n1512:             memory: \"512Mi\"\n1513:           requests:\n1514:             cpu: \"100m\"\n\n(Output capped at 50 KB. Showing lines 1-1514. Use offset=1515 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# pkg/workloadmanager — WorkloadManager HTTP Service Framework Design\n\n## AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP Service Framework\n\n**Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n**Language**: Go  \n**Size**: M  \n**Purpose**: Provide HTTP API for creating and managing agent runtime sandboxes, implementing session lifecycle management, and integrating with Kubernetes API and Redis storage.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Package Structure\n\n```\npkg/workloadmanager/\n├── api/\n│   ├── agent_runtime.go       # AgentRuntime CRUD handlers\n│   ├── code_interpreter.go    # CodeInterpreter CRUD handlers\n│   ├── sandbox.go             # Sandbox creation endpoints\n│   ├── middleware.go          # Authentication, logging, recovery","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/workloadmanager/design.md","time":{"start":1775843073820,"end":1775843073837}}}}
